President Obama expressed his condolences on the passing of Nigerian President Umaru Yar'Adua. He praised Yar'Adua's personal decency, integrity, and commitment to public service. Yar'Adua was known for promoting peace and stability in Africa and working towards peace and prosperity within Nigeria. President Obama highlighted the strong bilateral relationship between Nigeria and the United States and assured the Nigerian people of their enduring partnership in addressing common challenges.